  "recaps": {
    "1": "Ciri continues her magical education with Yennefer while political tensions escalate. Various factions seek to capture or control her, with Rience continuing his relentless pursuit.",
    "2": "Plans are made for Ciri to attend the magical academy at Aretuza for advanced training. The Council of Mages prepares to convene on Thanedd Island to discuss the growing political crisis.",
    "3": "The Council of Mages meets on Thanedd Island with Ciri attending Aretuza. Political tensions reach a breaking point as various factions position themselves around Ciri's fate and the growing war with Nilfgaard.",
    "4": "The coup at Thanedd erupts into violence as Vilgefortz reveals his true intentions. Ciri becomes separated from Geralt and Yennefer in the chaos, while the magical community tears itself apart.",
    "5": "The aftermath of the coup leaves the magical community shattered. Ciri remains missing while Geralt and his allies struggle to understand what happened and search for her.",
    "6": "The consequences of the coup ripple outward as various factions reposition themselves. New threats emerge while Ciri's location remains unknown, setting the stage for the larger conflict to come."
  }
